<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef">
  <CalDefFileVersion>16</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>2/19/15</Date>
    <Description>Fixed Application ordering Cal. You can now select which apps you want in which slot on the home screen or you can set it to none. Also added Driver Workload restriction</Description>
    <Author>Samer Khatib</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>6/12/2015</Date>
    <Description>Updated the default value for the ApplicationOrdering8 CAL from MirrorLink = 0x9 to AndroidAuto = 0xA within this caldef file</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>9/3/2015</Date>
    <Description>Within this CalDef file per request from Sanghyun Ryu, updated CAL usage for the Navigation_Zone_Enabled CAL to not show Low Radio usage.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>12/1/2015</Date>
    <Description>Within this CalDef file, updated the default values for ApplicationOrdering2 CAL through ApplicationOrdering16 CAL (Omitting value settings for the MirrorLink and Text icons for these CALs since there not intended to be used) to match the MY18 Default Application Ordering shown in the GIS-501.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>6/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Updated the initial default home screen calibration enumeration sort order positioning to match the HomeScreen icon order shown in the latest version GIS-501. Also, added ApplicationOrdering20 through ApplicationOrdering24 to account for the additional home screen sort order postioning needed for this. Note, this is intended to represent the initial default home screen calibration order positioning, which can be calibrated as needed to update the initial default position ordering. Also added new enable application calibrations for each home appplication for the purpose of adding or removing the given home screen application icon as defined by these enable calibrations in the position on the home screen set by the ApplicationOrdering calibrations.  </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>7/1/2016</Date>
    <Description>Updated the description for the APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CLIMATE_ENABLED calibration to note both the Global A or Global B Climate feature calibrations, HvacRadioDisplayEnable (Global A specific calibration) or Climate Application Available (Global B specific calibration), to use as the first/overriding condition for determining if the Climate HomeScreen application icon shall be displayed or not.  Also, updated the description for APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_REARCLIMATE_ENABLED to note both the Global A or Global B RearClimate feature calibrations,  RearHvacRadioDisplayEnable (Global A specific calibration) or 2.) Rear_Climate_Application_Available (Global B specific calibration), to use as the first/overriding condition for determining if the RearClimate HomeScreen application icon shall be displayed or not.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>10/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file added the APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_WIFIHOTSPOT_ENABLED and APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_TRAILERING_ENABLED calibrations, and deleted the APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_TEXT_ENABLED calibration since as noted in the GIS-501 the Text App is no longer needed as a possible App that could need to be added in the default HomeScreen list. Also updated the default value for the HomeScreen ApplicationOrdering calibrations to match the updated ordering shown in the GIS-501 Home Screen UI V4 Climate Ordering- Snippit-1 14OCT2016 as a part of the update in RTC CR#: 1112145.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>1/23/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef file for RTC CR#: 1153650, updated the default value for the default ordering ApplicationOrdering14 through ApplicationOrdering20 calibrations to match the HomeScreen icon order shown in latest version GIS-501.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>6/13/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef file made the following updates: 1.) Updated the description of the APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_BAIDUCARLIFE_ENABLED calibration to note the BAIDUCARLIFE feature calibration (ENABLE_APPLICATIONBAIDU_CARLIFE) from the GIS-513 to factor in the criteria for whether or not the BAIDUCARLIFE homescreen application icon gets dispayed. 2.) Updated the description for the ENABLE_APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_INTERIOR_ENABLED calibration to note the correct feature calibration to use for this feature is AmbientLightingEnable, not the previously noted ENABLE_APPLICATION_INTERIOR_LIGHTING calibration in the description of this calibration., and  3.) Also, updated the usage field for all of the calibration in this caldef file to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>10/1/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef file, added GEM usage to all of the calibrations within this caldef except for the Navigation_Zone_Enabled calibration. Since the Navigation_Zone_Enabled calibration was the only calibration within this caldef file that did not fall within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>1/25/2018</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef file made the following updates for CR#: 1529732:: Added APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_AIRQUALITY_ENABLED calibration shown in the GIS-501 and GIS-551. Updated the default value for  ApplicationOrdering20 through ApplicationOrdering25 to reflect the latest MY20 Default Application ordering to account for the additon of the AirQuality HomeScreen App. Also, added new ApplicationOrdering26 calibration to account for the shifting down of the default values of ApplicationOrdering20 through ApplicationOrdering25 calibrations, and with this reflect the latest MY20 Default Application ordering shown in GIS-501 with the additon of the AirQuality HomeScreen App.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>09/17/2018</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#1897607, Updated GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef with ApplicationOrdering27 = Vehicle Information, ApplicationOrdering28 = APA, and ApplicationOrdering29 = Owner&#x2019;s Manual, APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_VEHICLEINFORMATION_ENABLED, APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_OWNERSMANUAL_ENABLED, and APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_APA_ENABLED</Description>
    <Author>Ibnul Khan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>10/30/2018</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#1686594, Updated GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef file with ApplicationOrdering30 = PA, and APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PA_ENABLED calibrations.</Description>
    <Author>Ibnul Khan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>9/28/2020</Date>
    <Description>Per CRs #2526202 and #2620007 adding several new cals and updating several default settings</Description>
    <Author>Greg Lindemann</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>16</Version>
    <Date>9/17/2021</Date>
    <Description>In support of CR#: 3098258, updated the GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef file to add the new calibration called APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PERFORMANCEAPP_ENABLED and added the new ApplicationOrdering44 calibration paired with the APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PERFORMANCEAPP_ENABLED to support enabling/disabling the Performance App on the home screen. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>17</Version>
    <Date>11/18/2021</Date>
    <Description>In support of CR#: 3105232, updated the GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef file to add the new calibration called APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_ALEXA_ENABLED.</Description>
    <Author>Greg Lindemann</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>18</Version>
    <Date>4/19/2023</Date>
    <Description>In support of CR#: 3381323, updated the GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef file to add the new calibration called APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_MAPSPLUS_ENABLED, APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_SPOTIFY_ENABLED, APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_IHEARTRADIO_ENABLED, APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_WEATHER_ENABLED</Description>
    <Author>Andrea Campbell</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration is used to enable the HP1 Performance App on the home screen. This calibration will need to be set to TRUE (ie: enabled) for any vehicle that requires the performance app.  The Performance App calibration is used to Enable/Disable the display of this Application on the HomeScreen. When this calibration is set to True(Enabled), this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration is set to False(Disabled), this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen." Name="APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PERFORMANCEAPP_ENABLED" References="GIS-501" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_JjMx0BgSEey1B_g7sgX8Bg</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>9/17/2021</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of this calibration to support CR#: 3098258. </Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="The Vehicle Information Application provides vehicle status information (e.g. Oil Life, Tire Pressure, etc.). The Vehicle Information calibration is used to Enable/Disable the display of this Application on the HomeScreen and in the App Tray. When this calibration is set to True(Enabled), this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration is set to False(Disabled), this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen." Name="APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_VEHICLEINFORMATION_ENABLED" References="GIS501 Section 5.1" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_e-mgwLtwEei-5bHnoORlAg</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="The PA application is an application that gives you the information about PA provided with the vehicle. The PA calibration is used to Enable/Disable the display of this Application on the HomeScreen. When this calibration is set to True (Enabled), this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen and in the App Tray. When this calibration is set to False (Disabled), this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen. " Name="APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PA_ENABLED" References="GIS501 SECTION 5.1" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_0BkNcdxPEeirwbrltDv1bw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
