  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="The Owner's manual application is an electronic version of the physical Owner's Manual that is typically provided with a vehicle. The Owner's Manual calibration is used to Enable/Disable the display of this Application on the HomeScreen and in the App Tray. When this calibration is set to True (Enabled), this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration is set to False(Disabled), this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen. " Name="APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_OWNERSMANUAL_ENABLED" References="GIS501 SECTION5.1" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALB,VCU">
