  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration is used to Enable/Disable the display of this Application on the HomeScreen and in the App Tray. Note: The first/overriding condition for determining if this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen is the value of the Climate feature calibration (HvacRadioDisplayEnable for Global A or Climate Application Available for Global B ). When the value of the HvacRadioDisplayEnable (Global A specific calibration) or Climate Application Available (Global B specific calibration) is set to False (Disabled), this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen no matter what the value of this calibration (APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CLIMATE_ENABLED) is set to. When the HvacRadioDisplayEnable (Global A specific calibration) or Climate Application Available (Global B specific calibration) is set to True, the value of the APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CLIMATE_ENABLED calibration is then used as the next/secondary condition for determining if this HomeScreeHomeScreen Appliation shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration (APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CLIMATE_ENABLED) is set to True (Enabled), this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration is set to False (Disabled), this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen. " Name="APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CLIMATE_ENABLED" References="GIS-501" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_RBdakDxFEeaGEeA8k3J6-w</CalID>
