  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration is used to Enable/Disable the display of this Application on the HomeScreen and in the App Tray. Note: The first/overriding condition for determining if this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen is the value of any of the PDR related calibrations (LVM_1, LVM_2, or LVM_3). If the value of none of the PDR related calibrations (LVM_1, LVM_2, or LVM_3) is set to a value other than LVM_PERFORMANCE_COMPUTER, this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen no matter what the value of this calibration (APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PDRLVM_ENABLED) is set to. If at least one of the PDR related calibrations (LVM_1, LVM_2, or LVM_3) is set to a value of LVM_PERFORMANCE_COMPUTER, then the value of the APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PDRLVM_ENABLED calibration is then used as the next/secondary condition for determining if this HomeScreeHomeScreen Appliation shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration (APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PDRLVM_ENABLED) is set to True (Enabled), this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration is set to False (Disabled), this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen." Name="APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_PDRLVM_ENABLED" References="GIS-501" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
