    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/13/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the description for the ENABLE_APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_INTERIOR_ENABLED calibration to note the correct feature calibration to use for this feature is AmbientLightingEnable, not the previously noted ENABLE_APPLICATION_INTERIOR_LIGHTING calibration in the description of this calibration. Also, updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>10/1/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
