  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration is used to Enable/Disable the display of this Application on the HomeScreen and in the App Tray. Note: The first/overriding condition for determining if this VPM Camera HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen is the value of VPM present configured calibration (RVS_PRESENT_STATUS). If the value of the VPM present configured calibration (RVS_PRESENT_STATUS) is set to a value other than PRESENT_VPM_CAMERA_PROCESSING_MODULE, this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen no matter what the value of this calibration (APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CAMERALVM_ENABLED) is set to. If the VPM present configured calibration (RVS_PRESENT_STATUS) is set to a value of PRESENT_VPM_CAMERA_PROCESSING_MODULE, then the value of the APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CAMERALVM_ENABLED calibration is then used as the next/secondary condition for determining if this HomeScreeHomeScreen Appliation shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration (APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CAMERALVM_ENABLED) is set to True (Enabled), this HomeScreen Application shall be displayed on the HomeScreen. When this calibration is set to False (Disabled), this HomeScreen Application shall not be displayed on the HomeScreen.    " Name="APPLICATION_HOMESCREEN_CAMERALVM_ENABLED" References="GIS-501" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
